    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="416" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Vignaud</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 12,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the request of the Venezuelan Government you will, with the
                            acquiescence of the Government of France, upon the retirement of
                            Venezuelan minister and upon application by him, afford your friendly
                            good offices for the protection of Venezuelan citizens in France; but
                            you will not represent Venezuela diplomatically, nor will consuls under
                            you act in official representation of Venezuela.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
